=== POST-HOC ADDENDUM (not pre-registered; noise-floor calibration) ===
The Arm B/C residual sums have per-point weights -2*(1_prime - pbar)
(Arm B) resp. per-class-centered indicators (Arm C), with Bernoulli
variance 4*pbar*(1-pbar) instead of lambda's variance 1.  Dividing the
raw rho by s = sqrt(4*pbar*(1-pbar)) compares each residual to the
random-noise floor OF ITS OWN VARIANCE:
   z    pfrac      s   rhoB/s  rhoC(0.5/H)/s  rhoC(2/H)/s
   700  0.641  0.959   0.960          0.779        1.031
  1000  0.676  0.936   0.976          0.792        1.034
  2000  0.757  0.858   1.008          0.820        1.050
  5000  0.895  0.613   1.059          0.855        1.101
All variance-adjusted ratios lie in 0.78-1.10 at every z, with no
z-trend above 1: after subtracting per-class (or even class-blind
global) S-P counting, the rational-point residual is statistically
indistinguishable from generic-alpha noise of the same variance.
(Arm C at delta=0.5/H sits slightly BELOW 1 because the per-class
model fits q class means and so absorbs part of the noise.)
